ent/shows/myhusbandslover/articles/2013-10-14/9127/One-More-Try-My-Husbands-Lover-The-Concert-spins-up-a-storm |title=One More Try: My Husband's Lover The Concert spins up a storm |publisher=[[GMA Network]]|date=October 14, 2013|accessdate=October 14, 2013}}</ref> It was broadcast in television by GMA Network on October 20, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/330734/showbiz/mhl-one-more-try-concert-mapapanood-sa-snbo-sa-oktubre-20|title='MHL: One More Try Concert' mapapanood sa SNBO sa Oktubre 20 |publisher=[[GMA Network]] |date=October 13, 2013 |accessdate=October 14, 2013}}</ref> According to [[AGB Nielsen Philippines]]' Mega Manila household ratings, the television broadcast of ''One More Try: My Husband's Lover The Concert'' earned an 11.9% rating.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/12792/agb-nielsen-mega-manila-household-ratings-october-14-to-20-2013-genesis-enters-top-10-my-husband39s- |title=AGB Nielsen Mega Manila Household Ratings (October 14 to 20, 2013): Genesis enters top 10; My Husband's Lover's finale beats Bukas Na Lang Kita Mamahalin |author=Tuazon, Nikko |date=October 29, 2013 |accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official site|http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/my_husbands_lover}}\n* {{IMDb title|2973256}}\n\n{{GMA Network (current and upcoming original programming)}}\n\n[[Category:GMA Network drama series]]\n[[Category:Philippine LGBT-related television shows]]\n[[Category:Philippine drama television series]]\n[[Category:2013 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2013 Philippine television series endings]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n[[Category:2010s LGBT-related drama television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2013 Philippine television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = My Husband's Lover\n| image = My Husband's Lover title card.jpg\n| caption = Title card\n| genre = {{plainlist|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Romance film|Romance]]}}\n| runtime = 30-45 minutes\n| creator = [[Suzette Doctolero]]\n| creative_director = [[Jun Lana]]\n| director = [[Dominic Zapata]]\n| executive_producer = Carolyn B. Galve\n| writer = {{plainlist|\n* Marlon Miguel\n* Geng Delgado\n* Jason Lim\n* Jonathan Cruz\n* Michelle Amog}}\n| cinematography = Roman Theodossis\n| starring = {{Plain list|\n* [[Dennis Trillo]]\n* [[Tom Rodriguez]]\n* [[Carla Abellana]]}}\n| theme_music_composer = {{plainlist|\n* Cecile Azarcon\n* Tata Betita}}\n| opentheme = \"One More Try\" (instrumental)\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| location = {{plainlist|\n* [[Quezon City]], Philippines\n* [[Subic, Zambales]], Philippines}}\n| language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n| network = [[GMA Network]]\n| company = GMA Entertainment TV\n| picture_format = [[480i]] ([[SDTV]])\n| camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| first_aired = {{start date|2013|6|10}}\n| last_aired = {{end date|2013|10|18}}\n| num_episodes = 94\n| website = http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/my_husbands_lover\n}}\n\n'''''My Husband's Lover''''' is a 2013 [[Philippine television drama]] romance series broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. The series is the first gay themed drama series in Philippine television. Directed by [[Dominic Zapata]], it stars [[Dennis Trillo]] in the title role, [[Tom Rodriguez]] and [[Carla Abellana]]. It premiered on June 10, 2013 on the network's Telebabad line up replacing ''[[Love & Lies]]'' and on June 11, 2013 worldwide on [[GMA Pinoy TV]]. The series concluded on October 18, 2013, with a total of 94 episodes.\n\nThe series is streaming online on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web|URL=https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGRhcC_vtOrbpclfrNOl11PqnV8Vd0fTV |title=My Husband's Lover (Full Episodes) - YouTube |accessdate=February 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\nVincent Soriano gets his girlfriend Lally pregnant while they were still in college. They marry and raise a family. While Vincent keeps a secret from his wife, he is gay. When Vincent's former male lover, Eric returns to his life, they have an affair until Lally catches them.<ref>{{cite web|URL=http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/my_husbands_lover/about/ |title=My Husband's Lover |accessdate=March 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Cast and characters ==\n{{Main|List of My Husband's Lover characters}}\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = Shake, Rattle and Roll XV Official Trailer - Dennis Trillo.jpg\n|caption1 = Dennis Trillo portrays Eric del Mundo.\n|width1 = 150\n|image2 = Carla Abellana, 2014 (cropped).jpg\n|caption2 = Carla Abellana portrays Lally Agatep-Soriano.\n|width2 = 150\n|image3 = Kuh Ledesma Philippine Pop Jazz Singer Commons.jpg\n|caption3 = Kuh Ledesma portrays Elaine Soriano.\n|width3 = 150\n}}\n\n<!--Official cast billing from GMA Network.-->\n;Lead cast\n* [[Dennis Trillo]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Eric Del Mundo|Eric del Mundo]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/gma/articles/2013-05-15/8628/Dennis-Trillo-paninindigan-ang-pagiging-bading|title=Dennis Trillo, paninindigan ang pagiging gay|publisher=[[GMA Network]]|date=May 15, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Tom Rodriguez]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Vincent Soriano|Vincent Soriano]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/38670/dennis-trillo-and-tom-rodriguez-play-gay-lovers-in-new-kapuso-soap-pledge-loyalty-to-popoy-caritativo|title=Dennis Trillo and Tom Rodriguez play gay lovers in new Kapuso soap; pledge loyalty to Popoy Caritativo|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=May 15, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224101624/http://www.pep.ph/news/38670/dennis-trillo-and-tom-rodriguez-play-gay-lovers-in-new-kapuso-soap-pledge-loyalty-to-popoy-caritativo|archive-date=December 24, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/38967/tom-rodriguez-says-role-in-my-husband39s-lover-opened-his-eyes-about-the-plight-of-closet-gays|title=Tom Rodriguez says role in My Husband's Lover opened his eyes about the plight of closet gays|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=June 6, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Carla Abellana]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Lally Agatep-Soriano|Lally Agatep-Soriano]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.journal.com.ph/index.php/entertainment/showbiz-news/50010-carla-to-star-in-my-husbands-lover|title=Carla to star in 'My Husband's Lover'|publisher=Journal Online|date=May 9, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130623075943/http://www.journal.com.ph/index.php/entertainment/showbiz-news/50010-carla-to-star-in-my-husbands-lover|archivedate=June 23, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/38962/carla-abellana-prefers-to-be-cheated-with-another-woman-than-with-a-man|title=Carla Abellana prefers to be cheated with another woman than with a man|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=June 5, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref>\n\n;Supporting cast\n* [[Pancho Magno]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Paul Salcedo|Paul Salcedo]]\n* [[Bettina Carlos]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Vicky Araneta|Vicky Araneta]]<ref name=\"Bettina\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/38937/bettina-carlos-on-working-again-with-dennis-trillo-in-my-husbandrsquos-lover-may-pag-asa-na-akong-pagnasaan-nang-kaunti-si-dennisrdquo|title=Bettina Carlos on working again with Dennis Trillo in My Husband's Lover: \"May pag-asa na akong pagnasaan nang kaunti si Dennis!\"|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=June 5, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Karel Marquez]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Evelyn Agatep|Evelyn Agatep]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/shows/myhusbandslover/videos/2013-06-06/23718/Not-Seen-on-TV-An-invite-from-Karel-Marquez|title=Not Seen on TV: An invite from Karel Marquez|publisher=[[GMA Network]]|date=June 6, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Kevin Santos]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Danny|Danny]]\n* [[Victor Basa]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#David|David]]<ref name=\"Victor\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/39013/victor-basa-on-his-respect-for-gays-ldquokapag-tinrato-mo-ang-isang-tao-with-respect-yoursquoll-get-respect-backrdquo|title=Victor Basa on his respect for gays: \"Kapag tinrato mo ang isang tao with respect, you\u2019ll get respect back.\"|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=June 8, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Freeman\">{{cite web|url=http://www.philstar.com/cebu-entertainment/2013/06/07/951210/victor-basa-gay-my-husbands-lover|title=Victor Basa is gay in \"My Husband\u2019s Lover\"|publisher=[[The Freeman (newspaper)|The Freeman]]|date=June 7, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Glydel Mercado]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Sandra Agatep|Sandra Agatep]]\n* [[Chanda Romero]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Soledad \"Sol\" Del Mundo|Sol del Mundo]]\n* [[Roi Vinzon]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Armando Soriano|Armando Soriano]]\n* [[Kuh Ledesma]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Elaine Soriano|Elaine Soriano]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/38959/kuh-ledesma-on-charice39s-revelation-it-is-best-na-yung-mga-ganoong-bagay-hindi-muna-sabihin|title=Kuh Ledesma on Charice's revelation: \"It is best na yung mga ganoong bagay, hindi muna sabihin.\"|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=June 4, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tempo.com.ph/2013/06/kuh-wala-pang-balak-mag-retire/#.UbVmo-eqksc|title=Kuh wala pang balak mag-retire|publisher=Tempo|date=June 8, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921055530/http://www.tempo.com.ph/2013/06/kuh-wala-pang-balak-mag-retire/#.UbVmo-eqksc#.UbVmo-eqksc|archive-date=September 21, 2013|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n;Recurring cast\n* Antone Limgenco as Diego \"Diegs\" Soriano\n* Elijah Alejo as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Diego and Hanna Soriano|Hanna \"Munchkin\" Soriano]]\n\n;Guest cast\n* [[Keempee de Leon]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Zandro \"Zsa Zsa\" Soriano|Zandro \"Zsa Zsa\" Soriano]]\n* [[Rodjun Cruz]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Martin Lizada|Martin Lizada]]\n* [[Roy Alvarez]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Manuel Soriano|Manuel Soriano]]\n* [[Mark Gil]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Galo Agatep|Galo Agatep]]\n* [[Chynna Ortaleza]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Stella|Stella]]\n* [[Ashley Cabrera]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Mikaella|Mikaella]]\n* [[Jaclyn Jose]] as [[List of Mundo Mo'y Akin characters#Do\u00f1a Charito Vda. de Carbonel|Charito Vda. de Carbonel]]\n* [[Ryan Agoncillo]] as [[List of My Husband's Lover characters#Sam|Sam]]\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Conception and development ===\n{|class=\"toccolours\" style=\"float:left; margin-left:1em; margin-right:2em; font-size:95%; width:28em; max-width:40%;\" cellspacing=\"5\"\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|\"I'm sure a lot of people are gonna say a thing or two about the show. All I really have to say is, this show is a love story. And love is a beautiful thing and it shines through no matter age, no matter race, no matter color, and no matter gender preference. Love is love and no matter what package it comes in, it's still beautiful.\"\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\" |\u2014 Series' director, Dominic Zapata on the show's theme<ref name= \"PEPphotos\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/photos/3826/carla-abellana-tom-rodriguez-and-dennis-trillo-topbill-my-husband39s-lover|title=Carla Abellana, Tom Rodriguez, and Dennis Trillo topbill My Husband's Lover|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=June 5, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref>\n|}\nSeries' creator [[Suzette Doctolero]] began developing the series in early 2013. It all started with her desire to create a non-traditional, out of the box yet has social relevance, truthful, emotional and with \"real\" characters stories. The idea for the series was conceived when Doctolero began thinking about the question: \"What would you do if you find out that you husband is cheating on you... with another man?\" Although the idea is not-an-easy-story-to-tell because of its controversial theme which touches on the sensitive issue of [[Homosexuality|homosexual]] and [[Bisexuality|bisexual]] relationships, Doctolero explained that \"the show is not all about the queerness of the characters but more of a love story and a family drama. When Doctolero presented the idea to [[GMA Network]], the management said \"yes\" easily because they found the concept interesting and \"it was based on the relatability of the masses to the topic.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ph.omg.yahoo.com/news/gay-themed-tv-series-my-husbands-lover-gma-network-101705251.html|title=Is the Philippines ready for a gay-themed daily series?|publisher=[[Yahoo!|Yahoo! Philippines]]|date=June 10, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref>\n\nCarolyn Galve served as the executive producer of the series throughout its run. [[Dominic Zapata]] was assigned to direct the show. Zapata said \"It's very refreshing for me to direct this material. The subject is really sensitive and I want to be accurate in portraying how gay people are and the dynamics of gay relationships so we did a lot of research. I don't want to make a mistake or make a misrepresentation.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbiz-portal.com/2013/06/my-husbands-lover-first-teleserye-to.html|title='My Husband's Lover' The First Teleserye To Seriously Tackle Homosexual Relationships|publisher=Showbiz Portal|date=June 6, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013}}</ref> Regarding the theme, Zapata stressed \"I'm sure a lot of people are gonna say a thing or two about the show. All I really have to say is, this show is a love story. And love is a beautiful thing and it shines through no matter age, no matter race, no matter color, and no matter gender preference. Love is love and no matter what package it comes in, it's still beautiful.\"<ref name= \"PEPphotos\" />\n\nFilming for the series began May 21, 2013. Many of the scenes were filmed on location in [[Quezon City]]. The show is designed for sixteen-week run.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/entertainment/34566-my-husbands-lover-behind-the-story|title=My Husband\u2019s Lover: Behind the story|publisher=Rappler|date=July 23, 2013|accessdate=July 23, 2013}}</ref> The show is extended for additional three weeks and concluded in October 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/39940/carla-abellana-returns-to-work-after-hospital-confinement-my-husband39s-lover-to-end-in-october|title=Carla Abellana returns to work after hospital confinement; My Husband's Lover to end in October|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=August 13, 2013|accessdate=August 13, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe series' program manager, Helen Rose Sese clarified that the show won't delve on the sensual aspects of relationships\u2014straight or not. \"The show's intention is not to promote gay and lesbian relationship, but more of a reflection that this is happening now. The creative team will also be under scrutiny to try and avoid noise on the part of religious groups. We also make sure we don\u2019t go beyond anything that will offend them, as well as the gay community.\" Sese also stressed that the network has informed the local censors' body on the potentially controversial series. The [[Movie and Television Review and Classification Board]] (MTRCB) has shown understanding of their material while warning them to observe certain limitations in presenting delicate scenes for general viewership.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tempo.com.ph/2013/05/gma-tests-market-thru-gay-themed-soap/#.UbAhTtKqksc|title=GMA tests market thru gay-themed soap|publisher=Tempo|date=May 11, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130606200321/http://www.tempo.com.ph/2013/05/gma-tests-market-thru-gay-themed-soap/#.UbAhTtKqksc|archive-date=June 6, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> The show has been approved without cuts by the MTRCB, albeit with an SPG or Strong Parental Guidance rating.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessmirror.com.ph/index.php/en/lifestyle/show/14754-with-my-husband-s-lover-gma-pushes-the-prime-time-envelope|title=With \u2018My Husband\u2019s Lover,\u2019 GMA pushes the prime-time envelope|publisher=[[BusinessMirror]]|date=June 10, 2013|accessdate=July 11, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130719191315/http://businessmirror.com.ph/index.php/en/lifestyle/show/14754-with-my-husband-s-lover-gma-pushes-the-prime-time-envelope#|archive-date=July 19, 2013|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nA kissing scene between Tom Rodriguez and Dennis Trillo was supposed to be aired in the finale but was not shown due to MTRCB guidelines. The scene could be seen in the DVD version of the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/40784/tom-rodriguez-disappointed-over-non-airing-of-kissing-scene-with-dennis-trillo-in-my-husband39s-lover|title=Tom Rodriguez disappointed over non-airing of kissing scene with Dennis Trillo in My Husband's Lover|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=October 18, 2013|accessdate=October 27, 2013}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\nThe series featured three main characters and nine prominent recurring characters throughout its run. [[Dennis Trillo]] and [[Carla Abellana]] were the first two actors to be cast for the lead roles. Abellana was cast as Lally Agatep-Soriano, a woman who struggles to be the perfect wife for the husband she loves who, in fact is a closeted gay. Although she described the series as \"a risky project\",<ref name=\"Carla\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/38581/carla-abellana-finally-stars-in-new-teleserye-after-nine-months-of-waiting|title=Carla Abellana finally stars in new teleserye after nine months of waiting|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=May 8, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref> Abellana didn't have qualms accepting the role. She loves that the series encompasses a wider audience which include straight, gay, lesbian, married or single audience. Trillo, on the other hand had recently finishing Temptation of Wife, was chosen to play Eric del Mundo, a gay architect and the lover of Lally\u2019s husband, Vincent Soriano. Trillo was originally cast as Vincent Soriano but he decided to play Eric del Mundo instead.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X3ETyzhW2Js|title=Kapuso Mo Jessica Soho-My Husband's Lover TomDen June 23, 2013|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=June 23, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref> Trillo is not new to gay roles. He already played gay characters in the past \u2013 most particularly in 2004 period film ''[[Aishite Imasu 1941: Mahal Kita]]'' where he won and was nominated in several acting awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manunuri.com/28th_gawad_urian_nominees_2005|title=28th Gawad Urian Nominees (2005)|publisher=[[Gawad Urian Award|Manunuri ng Pelikulang Pilipino]]|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1387739/awards|title=Dennis Trillo - Awards|publisher=[[IMDb]]|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[Tom Rodriguez]] was chosen to portray Vincent Soriano, a closeted gay, from many actors who auditioned for the said role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mb.com.ph/Entertainment/Entertainment_Main/16058/Tom_Rodriguez_is_100%25_sure_of_his_sexuality#.UbSMBOeqksc|title=Tom Rodriguez is 100% sure of his sexuality|publisher=[[Manila Bulletin]]|date=June 7, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615141701/http://mb.com.ph/Entertainment/Entertainment_Main/16058/Tom_Rodriguez_is_100%25_sure_of_his_sexuality#.UbSMBOeqksc#.UbSMBOeqksc|archive-date=June 15, 2013|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Rodriguez had to go through tests before being cast. He recently left ABS-CBN and signed GMA Network to appear in the show. During his audition, Rodriguez acted one scene\u2014a break-up scene\u2014with Trillo. Zapata described Rodriguez as \"the perfect Vincent\" among the many actors who auditioned for the role, said that \"[While] the others treated homosexuality as a disease, Tom interpreted it with so much understanding, and that's what we're looking for.\" Rodriguez described his role as very complex and demanding as the whole conflict of the show lies in his character. Rodriguez said, to prepare for the project, he watched gay-themed films like ''[[Brokeback Mountain]]'' and ''[[Love of Siam]]'' and talked to people with similar stories.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/98425/tom-rodriguez-not-homophobic|title=Tom Rodriguez \u2018not homophobic\u2019|publisher=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=June 13, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref> He also did research and found out that \"homosexual love is not really different from a heterosexual one. But of course things are more difficult for them because of all the social biases that exist.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.journal.com.ph/index.php/entertainment/showbiz-news/51854-truths-about-stars-that-should-be-kept-private|title=Truths about stars that should be kept private|publisher=Journal|date=June 8, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130610084545/http://www.journal.com.ph/index.php/entertainment/showbiz-news/51854-truths-about-stars-that-should-be-kept-private|archivedate=June 10, 2013}}</ref>\n\nSinger [[Kuh Ledesma]] was signed on to portray Elaine Soriano, after reading the week 1 script. The role Armando Soriano was originally offered to [[Phillip Salvador]] but he turned it down, so the role went to [[Roi Vinzon]]. [[Bettina Carlos]] was signed on to play \"the young cougar\" Vicky Araneta, and said that \"My role is seemingly simple but it's a challenge to make the cougar come out and give life to a young cougar.\"<ref name=\"Bettina\" /> [[Victor Basa]] originally auditioned for the role of Vincent Soriano, but ended up portraying David, Vincent's all-out gayfriend and ex-lover.<ref name=\"Carla\" /> Basa finds his role quite difficult in the sense that he doesn't want his character to look \"stereotype\" or just like any other homosexual role seen in media.\n\n== Music ==\nThe main theme song of ''My Husband's Lover'' is \"One More Try\" by [[Kuh Ledesma]], who also portrays Elaine Soriano in the show. This song is also  heard in the opening and ending credits of the show. The song was written by well-known composer [[:tl:Cecile Azarcon|Cecile Azarcon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philmusicregistry.net/main/song/view/2955|title=Philippine Music Registry: \"One More Try\"|publisher=Organisasyon ng Pilipinong Mang-aawit|accessdate=July 23, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150623100206/http://www.philmusicregistry.net/main/song/view/2955|archive-date=June 23, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was released in 1984 and part of the album ''I Think I'm in Love'' and under the now-defunct Blackgold Records.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kuhledesma.net/kuh_discography.html|title=Kuh Ledesma Discography|publisher=Kuh Ledesma Official Website|date=|accessdate=July 23, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe secondary theme song, \"Help Me Get Over\" by [[Jonalyn Viray]] and was written by Tata Betita.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdbaby.com/cd/jonalynviray|title=cdbaby: Jonalyn Viray EP|publisher=[[cdbaby]]|date=|accessdate=July 23, 2013}}</ref> It is taken out from ''Jonalyn Viray EP'' which was released in May 19, 2013. The EP was produced by Creative Media Entertainment and distributed by [[Universal Records (Philippines)|Universal Records]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ph/album/jonalyn-viray-ep/id650280135|title=iTunes: Jonalyn Viray EP|publisher=[[iTunes]]|date=|accessdate=July 23, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOther songs \"Sabihin Mo Naman\" and \"Ayoko Na\" were sung by [[Kris Lawrence]] and composed by himself and Noah Zuniga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cVeptOLceYgIt|title=Sabihin Mo Naman Official Music Video|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=March 19, 2013|accessdate=August 13, 2013}}</ref> It was the first single of his third album ''Spread the Love''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/records/articles/2013-06-10/30/Spread-the-Love-with-Kris-Lawrence|title=\u2018Spread the Love\u2019 with Kris Lawrence|publisher=[[GMA Network]]|date=June 10, 2013|accessdate=August 13, 2013}}</ref> While \"Ayoko Na\", by [[Jessa Zaragoza]] is composed by her husband, [[Dingdong Avanzado]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GQ99nLUUVlI|title=Ayoko Na Official Music Video|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=August 11, 2013|accessdate=August 13, 2013}}</ref> It is the third single from her album ''Pag Wala Na Ang Ulan''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/guide/guide/10563/jessa-zaragoza-releases-new-album-pag-wala-na-ang-ulan-talks-about-family-life|title=Jessa Zaragoza releases new album, Pag Wala Na Ang Ulan; talks about family life|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=July 19, 2012|accessdate=August 13, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Ratings===\nAccording to [[AGB Nielsen Philippines]]' Mega Manila household television ratings, the pilot episode of ''My Husband's Lover'' earned a 22.8% rating.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/guide/agb/12109/agb-nielsen-mega-manila-household-ratings-june-10-to-16-2013-ina-kapatid-anak-final-episode-tops-pri |title=AGB Nielsen Mega Manila Household Ratings (June 10 to 16, 2013): Ina Kapatid Anak final episode tops primetime; Sunday All Stars beats rival program on pilot episode |author=Tuazon, Nikko |date=June 21, 2013 |accessdate=January 25, 2018}}</ref> While the final episode scored a 25.3% rating.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/guide/agb/12792/agb-nielsen-mega-manila-household-ratings-october-14-to-20-2013-genesis-enters-top-10-my-husband39s-|title=AGB Nielsen Mega Manila Household Ratings (October 14 to 20, 2013): Genesis enters top 10; My Husband's Lover's finale beats Bukas Na Lang Kita Mamahalin |author=Tuazon, Nikko |date=October 29, 2013 |accessdate=January 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\nThe series garnered a positive response from professional critics, noting network's move in producing an \"out-of-the-box\" television series.<ref name=\"netizens\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/312422/showbiz/netizens-rave-over-my-husband-s-lover-pilot-episode|title=Netizens rave over 'My Husband\u2019s Lover' pilot episode|publisher=[[GMA Network]]|date=June 11, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref> The show was featured on June 17, 2013 issue of UK-based [[LGBT]] global news website ''[[Gay Star News]]''. It noted that the first episode of ''My Husband's Lover'' for its \"mature, nuanced and honest depiction of gay characters.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gaystarnews.com/article/gay-tv-drama-creates-buzz-philippines170613|title=Gay TV drama creates buzz in the Philippines|publisher=[[Gay Star News]]|date=June 17, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mb.com.ph/Entertainment/Entertainment_Main/17793/#.UcBp3ueqksc|title='My Husband\u2019s Lover' cited by international LGBT news site|publisher=[[Manila Bulletin]]|date=June 18, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622131358/http://mb.com.ph/Entertainment/Entertainment_Main/17793#.UcBp3ueqksc|archive-date=June 22, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn his review, Walden Sadiri M. Belen of ''[[Manila Bulletin]]'' responded well to the story, the ensemble's performances, and the director, said that \"the story, unconventional and provocative as it is, was treated beautifully and convincingly. The subject matter \u2014 a married man and a father having an affair with another man \u2014 could  be controversial considering the relatively conservative nature of Filipinos, but so far the series have been decent in presentation and treatment which is fast-paced too. And most noticeable was the remarkable portrayal of the main cast in their respective roles [...]. They are credible in their performances, and especially noted was [[Tom Rodriguez]]'s portrayal of a closet gay who is, ironically, the son of an army general. But all the other members of the cast also delivered A-1 performances: [[Kuh Ledesma]], [[Victor Basa]], [[Glydel Mercado]] and [[Karel Marquez]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mb.com.ph/Entertainment/Entertainment_Main/16966/Praises_heaped_on_cast_of_#.UblUXOeqksc|title=Praises heaped on cast of 'My Husband's Lover'|publisher=[[Manila Bulletin]]|date=June 13, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130617024818/http://mb.com.ph/Entertainment/Entertainment_Main/16966/Praises_heaped_on_cast_of_#.UblUXOeqksc|archive-date=June 17, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Radio and TV personality and ''Manila Bulletin'' columnist [[Mr. Fu]] praised the show and its cast, said that \"the show was beautiful, moving, interesting and promising. It has very interesting characters played by credible actors [...]. [[Carla Abellana]], for one, is able to make audiences feel her love for her mother and husband in the story. She has this very fresh television presence, that you would love to watch her every now and then. Dennis [Trillo] has already proven his acting talent and he does not fail on this show. A best example of a cute \"gay who is not so gay\", he knows when to use his eyes, his mouth, his whole body to portray the \"gayness\". Tom, on the other hand, can portray that \"paminta\" (closeted gay) character with confidence, and charm that makes him appealing on screen. Their on-cam chemistry also makes them effective in their roles. The way they trade lines is believable and their body language seems very natural. Their \"revolving glass door\" scene where they accidentally meet after years of not communicating was so romantic and intense.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mb.com.ph/Entertainment/Entertainment_Main/18018/The_new_love_team_to_beat%C2%A0#.UcKQgueqksc|title=The new love team to beat|publisher=[[Manila Bulletin]]|date=June 20, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627080417/http://mb.com.ph/Entertainment/Entertainment_Main/18018/The_new_love_team_to_beat%C2%A0#.UcKQgueqksc|archive-date=June 27, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n''Journal''{{'}}s resident entertainment columnist Butch Roldan also reserved high praise for the show, said that \"the series explains in a broad spectrum that love cannot be defined by sexual preference alone, that love has its own understanding of what is right and wrong and is ready to suffer even under very harsh circumstances.\"<ref name=\"Journal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.journal.com.ph/index.php/entertainment/showbiz-news/52107-understanding-and-accepting-gay-relationships|title=Understanding and accepting gay relationships|publisher=Journal|date=June 12, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130613133300/http://www.journal.com.ph/index.php/entertainment/showbiz-news/52107-understanding-and-accepting-gay-relationships|archive-date=June 13, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>''Journal''{{'}}s entertainment columnist, Mario Bautista gave it a mixed review, said that \"The series should have started in the thick of things, since the title and the trailers have already shown where the story is going. Dennis [Trillo] should have been there from the start and then they just go back to how the story all started.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.journal.com.ph/index.php/entertainment/showbiz-news/52199-toni-the-oldest-but-has-longest-relationship|title=Toni the oldest but has longest relationship|publisher=Journal|date=June 13, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130616072805/http://www.journal.com.ph/index.php/entertainment/showbiz-news/52199-toni-the-oldest-but-has-longest-relationship|archive-date=June 16, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nTelevision and film director [[Jose Javier Reyes]] congratulated the network \"for taking a risk & giving a fresh take on the tired templates of the telenovelas for something new.\"<ref name=\"netizens\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/news/39465/Joey-Reyes-commends-GMA-7-for-taking-risk-on-My-Husbands-Lover|title=Joey Reyes commends GMA-7 for taking risk on My Husband's Lover|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=July 10, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"toccolours\" style=\"float:left; margin-left:1em; margin-right:2em; font-size:95%; width:28em; max-width:40%;\" cellspacing=\"5\"\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|\"It feels like a lot of brainpower went into the preparation of the show. Some elements are borderline meticulous, like choosing to add a variety of gay characters to battle the gay stereotype head-on.\"\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\" |\u2014 Mark Angelo Ching, PEP<ref name=\"COMMENTARY: My Husband's Lover\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/12113/commentary-my-husband39s-lover|title=COMMENTARY: My Husband's Lover|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=June 22, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref>\n|}\n[[LGBT]] advocate and the author of \"Of God and Men: A Life in the Closet\", Atty. Raymond Alikpala reviewed \"GMA Network deserves congratulations for daring to go down this road less travelled. Eschewing the stereotypical storylines and cardboard clich\u00e9 characters, the writers of ''My Husband's Lover'' are depicting homosexual persons as no different from heterosexuals, which is radical in these parts. Homosexual characters have long been television staples, but they have been limited to supporting roles and comic relief. The series' non-stereotypical depiction of gay men can accomplish what [[Ladlad]] failed to do, which is to bring LGBT awareness into the mainstream of Filipino consciousness. Positive media depictions of LGBT persons are crucial in encouraging greater acceptance and recognition of our fundamental equality.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/312925/lifestyle/reviews/my-husband-s-lover-where-gays-are-not-clich-eacute-s|title='My Husband\u2019s Lover,' where gays are not clich\u00e9s|publisher=[[GMA Network]]|date=June 14, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref>\n\nAllan Diones of ''[[Abante Tonite]]'' said that \"[[Dennis Trillo]] and Tom Rodriguez has good screen chemistry [and] they are both excellent actors and can feel the emotions of their characters.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abante-tonite.com/issue/june1713/showbiz_others01.htm#.UcBlzdg7tla|title=Pamhintambalang TomDen, nakakakilig!|publisher=[[Abante Tonite|Abante-Tonite]]|date=June 17, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622054423/http://www.abante-tonite.com/issue/june1713/showbiz_others01.htm#.UcBlzdg7tla|archive-date=June 22, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n''[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]'''s Mark Angelo Ching praised [[Suzette Doctolero]] and [[Dominic Zapata]] for \"how the show looks polished. It feels like a lot of brainpower went into the preparation of the show. Some elements are borderline meticulous, like choosing to add a variety of gay characters to battle the gay stereotype head-on.\" He even added that \"unlike other shows that only depicts homosexual men as lustful beasts, or as sidekicks in crass, laughable situations, ''My Husband's Lover'' shows its gay characters in normal, everyday situations: going to the gym, working in an office, or relaxing at home. The characters have successful lives not as beauticians or stand-up comedians, but as architects and businessmen.\" Closing the review, he further added that the show \"is progressive\u2014a unique creation in today\u2019s media landscape where gay men are mostly relegated as sidekicks who provide comic relief. Let\u2019s hope that MHL continues to present homosexuals far from their clich\u00e9 images on television.\"<ref name=\"COMMENTARY: My Husband's Lover\"/>\n\nThe show is under the scrutiny of the [[Catholic Bishops' Conference of the Philippines]] - Episcopal Commission on Youth (CBCP-ECY) according to its  executive secretary, Father Conegundo Garganta. He added that television producers and writers should study themes being shown to the viewers, especially to the younger ones, and should be based on moral standards. In response to the CBCP statement, the [[Malaca\u00f1ang]] and [[MTRCB]] urged viewers to report any complaints about the show if they saw any unacceptable content against its SPG rating.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/entertainment/32114-my-husbands-lover-cbcp-govt|title='My Husband's Lover' under CBCP scrutiny|publisher=Rappler|date=June 25, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref> The [[GMA Network]] responded that they would continue to comply with MTRCB policies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/entertainment/32241-gma-my-husbands-lover|title=GMA-7 defends 'My Husband's Lover'|publisher=Rappler|date=June 26, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe show even impacted the [[Philippine politics]]. On July 19, the [[House of Representatives of the Philippines|House of Representatives]] held a \"mock\" session for the new representatives which was about investigating the possible ending of the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/318298/showbiz/chikaminute/ending-ng-my-husband-s-lover-iimbestigahan-ng-kongreso|title=Ending ng 'My Husband's Lover,' iimbestigahan ng Kongreso?|publisher=[[GMA Network]]|date=July 19, 2013|accessdate=July 20, 2013}}</ref> On August 8, 2013, [[Legislative districts of Albay|Albay - 1st District]] representative [[Edcel Lagman]] filed the House Bill 2352 in the [[16th Congress of the Philippines|16th Congress]]. He called it the ''My Husband's Lover'' bill which seeks to expand the scope of Article 333 of the [[Revised Penal Code of the Philippines|Revised Penal Code]] which only imposes punishment for a spouse having a sexual intercourse to another person of the opposite sex, other than their husband/wife. With this bill, it will add same-sex [[adultery]] to provide equality in the society.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/321162/news/nation/my-husband-s-lover-bill-seeks-to-punish-same-sex-adultery|title='My Husband's Lover' bill seeks to punish same-sex adultery|publisher=[[GMA Network]]|date=August 8, 2013|accessdate=August 10, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/35954-lagman-same-sex-adultery-bill|title='My Husband's Lover' bill: Penalize same-sex adultery|publisher=Rappler|date=August 8, 2013|accessdate=August 10, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipient\n! Result\n! Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2013\n| [[White Party]] Manila / Malate Business Association\n| Plaque of Appreciation\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''My Husband's Lover''\n| {{Won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/315420/showbiz/my-husband-s-lover-kinilala-ng-lgbt-community-sa-white-party-manila|title='My Husband's Lover,' kinilala ng LGBT community sa White Party Manila|publisher=[[GMA Network]]|date=July 1, 2013|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[27th PMPC Star Awards for Television]]\n| Best Primetime Drama Series\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.twitlonger.com/show/n_1rrb848 |title=NOMINEES 27th PMPC Star Awards for Television |publisher=Twitlonger |date=November 8, 2013 |accessdate=November 8, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Drama A